In this article, the White House Office of the Press Secretary shares a Christmas message from President Barack Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama. They express their well wishes to families across the country and encourage Americans to support members of the Armed Forces and their families during the holiday season. The Obamas highlight the importance of simple gifts and spending time with loved ones, as well as the need to help those less fortunate. They also acknowledge the sacrifices made by military personnel and their families, and urge Americans to find ways to support them. The article provides links to listen to the full message and watch a video of it.